race.comment: BE QUIET (3) resumed for new trainer Kim Waugh and ran fourth at Canterbury over 1100m and then dropped in class at Gosford last start 16 days ago to win easily as the favourite over 1100m. Well placed again in a race that is not much harder, and she is capable of repeating the dose. EQUILIBRIST (4) has needed both if his runs since returning from a spell, the latest a fifth over 1200m at Wyong a fortnight ago. He has more to offer, and all of his 3 career victories have come here on his home track. He is a strong each-way chance this time. BUTTERFLY STYLE (9) is a very progressive mare who kicked off her season over 1100m at Mudgee, and proved too strong, scoring by nearly a length. She has been a late scratching since then, and if she has not missed any work, then she is a big threat again. CRYPTONIC (1) resumes from a spell as a gelding for the first time. He comes to hand quickly and can't be taken lightly. SPICE BABY (10) is a very promising local gelding resuming. Each way.
